Bob Amsberry https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bob_Amsberry 0 Robert Wayne Amsberry (June 2, 1928—November 21, 1957) was an American actor, and one of the original cast members on the first two seasons of Walt Disney's The Mickey Mouse Club, working as both a writer and actor. Amsberry also worked as a voice actor, with a posthumous credit in Disney's Sleeping Beauty (1959).
